  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IA QM of participation in Local Planning</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sightsavers&#x2019; Citizenship and Political Participation work includes a focus on increasing the inclusivity of local development processes, plans and implementation. As such, Sightsavers is piloting a new approach to measure progress in the level of participation of people with disabilities (individual / OPD members) in local development processes, and progress of the level of inclusivity in the planning and implementation of local development plans. The tools have been drafted and scoped remotely due to COVID-19, including two remote workshops (one Cameroon and one in Senegal) with key stakeholders such as local council members, OPDs and CSO representatives. They need piloting in-country with stakeholders to test, learn and adapt the tools before they can be rolled out. Piloting is therefore planned for 2022 when we hope local and international travel will go ahead.</narrative>
  </description>
